-- =============================================================================
-- FORMAL VERIFICATION SPECIFICATIONS (Agda, Quint, TLA+)
-- =============================================================================
-- These sections define the formal properties that must be verified by
-- external proof systems. Allium captures the behavioral intent; the formal
-- tools verify the mathematical properties.

-- ─── Agda (Dependent Types — Compile-Time Safety Proofs) ─────────────────────
-- File: proofs/agda/BootSequence.agda
--
-- Agda verifies TYPE-LEVEL properties that Rust's type system cannot express:
--
-- 1. Boot Phase Monotonicity:
--    ∀ (b : BootSequence) → phase(b, t+1) ≥ phase(b, t)
--    "Boot phases never regress — preflight → foundation → ... → swarm"
--
-- 2. Quorum Preservation During Upgrade:
--    ∀ (g : Genome) (t : Time) → upgrading(g, t) → quorum_count(g, t) ≥ ⌊N/2⌋ + 1
--    "Quorum maintained throughout rolling upgrades (SC-SIL4-011)"
--
-- 3. Dying Gasp Totality:
--    ∀ (c : Container) → terminates(c) → ∃ (cp : DyingGaspCheckpoint) → saved(cp, c)
--    "Every container termination produces a checkpoint (SC-SIL4-007)"
--
-- 4. OODA Decision Exhaustiveness:
--    ∀ (obs : Observation) (ori : Orientation) → ∃! (d : Decision) → decides(obs, ori, d)
--    "Every observation/orientation pair produces exactly one decision"
--
-- 5. Genome Completeness:
--    |genome.containers| = 16 ∧ |built| + |pulled| + |shared| = 16
--    "Genome always has exactly 16 containers across 3 categories"
--
-- @guidance
--   Agda proofs run at compile time. They verify properties BEFORE deployment.
--   Use for: type-level invariants, totality proofs, termination proofs.
--   Do NOT use for: runtime behavior, temporal properties, concurrent properties.

-- ─── Quint (Executable Specification — State Machine Exploration) ─────────────
-- File: specs/quint/ignition.qnt
--
-- Quint verifies STATE MACHINE properties via bounded model checking:
--
-- 1. Boot DAG Acyclicity:
--    action boot_tier(tier) = { topo_sorted(dag) and not has_cycle(dag) }
--    "DAG is acyclic before every tier boot (SC-BOOT-008)"
--
-- 2. Health Hysteresis Convergence:
--    temporal always(flapping_detected implies eventually(stable_state))
--    "Hysteresis controller always reaches stable state within N checks"
--
-- 3. OODA Cycle Termination:
--    temporal always(cycle_started implies eventually(cycle_completed))
--    "Every OODA cycle completes (no infinite loops in decide phase)"
--
-- 4. Cascade Containment Bound:
--    invariant cascade_depth <= MAX_CASCADE_DEPTH (3)
--    "Cascade depth never exceeds 3 before apoptosis triggers"
--
-- 5. Rule Engine Determinism:
--    action eval_rules(facts) = { same_facts implies same_decision }
--    "Identical facts always produce identical GRL rule evaluation"
--
-- 6. Container Health Reachability:
--    temporal always(unreachable implies eventually(healthy or terminated))
--    "Unreachable containers are either recovered or terminated"
--
-- @guidance
--   Quint specs are executable — they can be simulated and model-checked.
--   Use for: state machine exploration, property-based testing, trace generation.
--   Integration: quint verify specs/quint/ignition.qnt --invariant all

-- ─── TLA+ (Temporal Logic — Distributed System Correctness) ──────────────────
-- File: specs/tlaplus/Ignition.tla
--
-- TLA+ verifies TEMPORAL LOGIC properties of the distributed 16-container mesh:
--
-- 1. Consensus Safety:
--    [](\A i, j \in ZenohRouters : Decided(i) /\ Decided(j) => Decision(i) = Decision(j))
--    "If two routers decide, they agree (SC-SIL4-006, 2oo3 voting)"
--
-- 2. Liveness — Boot Completion:
--    WF_vars(TierBoot) => <>(boot_phase = "swarm")
--    "Under weak fairness, boot eventually reaches swarm phase"
--
-- 3. Split-Brain Prevention:
--    [](partition_detected => <>(fenced_minority \/ recovered))
--    "Network partitions are always resolved by fencing or recovery"
--
-- 4. Apoptosis Progress:
--    [](apoptosis_triggered => <>(phase = "container_kill"))
--    "Apoptosis always progresses to completion (no stuck shutdown)"
--
-- 5. OODA Fairness:
--    WF_vars(OodaCycle) => [](Len(pending_observations) > 0 => <>(processed))
--    "All observations are eventually processed by the OODA loop"
--
-- 6. Zenoh Message Ordering:
--    [](\A m1, m2 \in Messages : sent(m1) < sent(m2) => received(m1) <= received(m2))
--    "Zenoh messages maintain causal ordering per topic"
--
-- @guidance
--   TLA+ is checked by the TLC model checker. It explores ALL reachable states.
--   Use for: distributed consensus, liveness, fairness, message ordering.
--   Integration: tlc2 specs/tlaplus/Ignition.tla -config Ignition.cfg

