-- |  7  | Recovery     | FMEA RPN matrix             | 20s        | L4    | SC-FMEA-004      |
-- |  8  | Fractal      | L0-L7 health tree           | 45s        | L0-L7 | SC-VER-074      |
-- |  9  | Security     | Axiom 0.1 enforcement       | 10s        | L0    | SC-IGNITE-002    |
-- | 10  | Logs         | tui-logger buffer           | 60s        | L1    | SC-LOG-001       |
-- | 11  | Agent UI     | CoT dialogue marquee        | 45s        | L5    | SC-AGUI-001      |
--
-- ─── INDRAJAAL Color Palette (SC-HMI-010) ───────────────────────────────────
-- CYAN:    RGB(0, 212, 170)    — accent, healthy, active tab
-- GREEN:   RGB(61, 214, 140)   — success, container running
-- YELLOW:  RGB(245, 166, 35)   — warning, degraded
-- RED:     RGB(224, 82, 82)    — error, critical, failed
-- MAGENTA: RGB(176, 82, 224)   — recovery, special
-- DIM:     RGB(78, 86, 104)    — muted, inactive
--
-- ─── Dark Cockpit 5-Mode (SC-HMI-010, prajna/dark_cockpit.gleam) ────────────
-- Dark:      No alerts → minimal gray, monochrome
-- Dim:       Warnings → subtle yellow, low-saturation
-- Normal:    Errors → visible orange, standard contrast
-- Bright:    Multiple errors → high-visibility, high-contrast
-- Emergency: Critical → full illumination + flash, red dominant
--
-- ─── Split-Screen Layout (SC-GLM-ZEN-003) ───────────────────────────────────
-- TOP  55%: Dashboard (sa-up dashboard, all 12 tabs)
-- BOTTOM 45%: Test Execution KPI Dashboard
-- Separator: "◄ TEST DASHBOARD ▼ ... ▲" (cyan)
-- Keyboard: Tab/Shift+Tab navigation, q/Esc quit, s/x/r/l container control
--
-- ─── Gleam Penta-Stack UI (SC-GLM-UI-001) ───────────────────────────────────
-- Every tab simultaneously exists as:
--   1. Rust Ratatui TUI (operator-facing, 12 tabs, port: CLI)
--   2. Gleam Lustre SSR Web UI (24 pages, port 4100)
--   3. Gleam Wisp REST API (14 endpoints, port 4100)
--   4. Gleam ANSI TUI (24 views, CLI)
--   5. F# Prajna CLI (safety fallback)

-- =============================================================================
-- TESTING SPECIFICATION
-- =============================================================================
-- Captures ALL testing requirements: Rust unit, Gleam gleeunit, E2E, coverage math

-- ─── Rust TUI Testing (SC-TUI-TEST-001..010) ────────────────────────────────
-- 7-Layer Testing Pyramid:
--   L1 Unit:        TestBackend + #[test] — all tabs × all states (<1s)
--   L2 Snapshot:    insta golden files — 10 tabs × 3 viewports (<3s)
--   L3 Style:       Buffer cell fg/bg assertions — all health colors (<1s)
--   L4 Integration: PTY harness — keyboard nav + tab cycling (<30s)
--   L5 Responsive:  Viewport matrix — 80×24 + 120×40 + 200×60 (<10s)
--   L6 Accessibility: Focus order verification (<60s)
--   L7 Visual:      Gemini closed-loop screenshot review (<45min)
--
-- Required per tab: >= 3 tests (default, loading, error states)
-- DashboardState::default() MUST be renderable
-- No render function may panic on empty/null data
-- Container health colors: GREEN=healthy, YELLOW=degraded, RED=critical

-- ─── Gleam gleeunit Testing (SC-GLM-TST-001..002) ──────────────────────────
-- Current: 1,721 tests, 0 failures (target: 100+ per release)
-- 8-Category Gold Standard (C1-C8):
--   C1 Page Structure (weight 1.0): Element count >= 5
--   C2 Status Badges  (weight 1.5): Healthy/Degraded/Critical visible
--   C3 Data Grids     (weight 1.0): >= 3 rows × 3 columns
--   C4 Timeline       (weight 0.8): Timestamp ordering
--   C5 Interactive    (weight 1.2): Click → state change
--   C6 Media/Rich     (weight 0.8): SVG/sparklines load
--   C7 AI Advisory    (weight 1.5): AG-UI events flow
--   C8 Action Button  (weight 3.0): Guardian + 2oo3 consensus
--
-- Per-tab monitoring: >= 30 seconds simulated via tick loops (SC-GLM-TST-002)
-- Coverage per page: 15 pages × 8 categories × Zenoh + monitoring tests

-- ─── Mathematical Coverage Gates (SC-MATH-COV-001..008) ─────────────────────
-- Shannon Entropy:  H = -Σ(p_i × log₂(p_i)) across C1-C8 ≥ 2.5 bits
-- CCM:              Σ(w_i × cov_i) / Σ(w_i) ≥ 0.90
-- Divergence:       |expected \ tested| / |expected| ≤ 0.10
-- FSI:              1 - (σ(H) / μ(H)) ≥ 0.85
-- ITQS:             0.25·H_norm + 0.35·CCM + 0.25·(1-D_EA) + 0.15·FSI ≥ 0.85
-- Grade:            A ≥ 0.90, B ≥ 0.85, C ≥ 0.75, D < 0.75
-- Weights:          [1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.0, 1.5, 2.5, 2.5, 3.0] for C1-C8

-- ─── BDD Levels (SC-BDD-001) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- 7 BDD levels per element:
--   BddUnit | BddIntegration | BddContract | BddComponent |
--   BddSystem | BddAcceptance | BddVisual
-- Coverage matrix: 15 pages × 12 elements × 7 levels = ~1,260 cells
-- Monitoring plan: 30-45s per element based on fractal layer criticality

-- ─── Fractal Matrix (testing/fractal_matrix.gleam) ──────────────────────────
-- TabElementInventory: per-page element enumeration with BDD coverage
-- ElementSpec: id, element_type, category (C1-C8), bdd_levels, monitoring_sec
-- BddCell: page × layer × level → test_count, covered

-- ─── Flight Check (testing/flight_check.gleam) ──────────────────────────────
-- 8 preflight checks: gleam_build, zenoh, containers, database, guardian, test_framework, cognitive, federation
-- Fractal RCA: 5-why chain mapped to L0-L7
-- Jidoka halt: L0, L1, L6 failures → mandatory halt (SC-TPS-001)

-- ─── Zenoh Test Observer (testing/zenoh_test_observer.gleam) ─────────────────
-- Records all OTel spans during test execution
-- Verifies: topics_received, message_ordering, span_completeness (4 OODA phases)
-- Enhanced: verify_all_pages_published (15 pages), verify_mcp_relay

-- ─── Gemini Pipeline Verification (testing/gemini_verification.gleam) ────────
-- OTel → Zenoh → MCP → Gemini pipeline end-to-end check
-- PipelineStage: OtelPublish, ZenohTransport, McpRelay, GeminiProcess
-- delivery_rate >= 0.9 for pipeline_healthy = true

-- ─── Graph-Theory Testing (SC-UIGT-001..015) ────────────────────────────────
-- Navigation digraph: |V|=22 pages, |E|~462, SCC=1, density=1.0
-- PageRank priority: Dashboard(0.055) > Cockpit(0.052) > Verification(0.050)
-- Chinese Postman bound: CPP ≈ 462 (all edges traversed)
-- Prime path coverage: >= 0.95 (Tier 1 pages), >= 0.80 (Tier 2)

-- ─── Human Intent Protection (SC-HINT-001..008) ─────────────────────────────
-- Alignment Score = |EXPECTED ∩ AS-IS| / |EXPECTED ∪ AS-IS|
-- ≥ 0.9: ALIGNED (green), 0.7-0.9: DRIFT (yellow), < 0.7: MISALIGNED (red, P1 alert)
-- Agent MUST NEVER modify Human-Specified Intent sections

-- =============================================================================
-- MATHEMATICAL STRUCTURES (Complete Inventory)
-- =============================================================================
-- All algorithms, formulas, metrics, and formal methods used across the system.
-- Each structure maps to a Gleam/Rust/F# implementation and STAMP constraint.

-- ─── INFORMATION THEORY ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 1. Shannon Entropy (H)
--    Formula: H = -∑(p_i × log₂(p_i)) for i in C1..C8
--    Range: [0.0, 3.0] bits (max = log₂(8) = 3.0 for 8 categories)
--    Gate: H ≥ 2.5 bits (SC-MATH-COV-001)
--    File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:91-119
--
-- 2. Normalized Shannon Entropy (H_norm)
--    Formula: H_norm = H / 3.0
--    Range: [0.0, 1.0]
--    File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:121-127
--    SC-MATH-COV-002
--
-- 3. Fleet Stability Index (FSI)
--    Formula: FSI = 1 - (σ(H) / μ(H)) clamped [0, 1]
--    σ = std deviation of entropy across suite, μ = mean entropy
--    Perfect stability: FSI = 1.0 (uniform entropy)
--    File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:187-204
--    SC-MATH-COV-005

-- ─── COVERAGE & QUALITY METRICS ─────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 4. Composite Coverage Metric (CCM)
--    Formula: CCM = ∑(w_i × cov_i) / ∑(w_i)
--    Weights W = [1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.0, 1.5, 2.5, 2.5, 3.0] for C1-C8
--    Gate: CCM ≥ 0.90 (SC-MATH-COV-003)
--    File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:129-163
--
-- 5. Element-Level Divergence (D_EA)
--    Formula: D_EA = |expected \ tested| / |expected|
--    Gate: D_EA ≤ 0.10 (SC-MATH-COV-004)
--    File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:165-185
--
-- 6. Integrated Test Quality Score (ITQS)
--    Formula: ITQS = 0.25×H_norm + 0.35×CCM + 0.25×(1-D_EA) + 0.15×FSI
--    Gate: ITQS ≥ 0.85 (SC-MATH-COV-006)
--    Grades: A≥0.90, B≥0.85, C≥0.75, D<0.75 (SC-MATH-COV-007)
--    File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:206-246

-- ─── SIMILARITY METRICS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 7. Jaccard Similarity (Human Intent Alignment)
--    Formula: J = |EXPECTED ∩ AS-IS| / |EXPECTED ∪ AS-IS|
--    Thresholds: ≥0.9 ALIGNED, 0.7-0.9 DRIFT, <0.7 MISALIGNED
--    File: testing/alignment.gleam:60-113
--    SC-HINT-003, SC-HINT-005

-- ─── GRAPH THEORY ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 8. PageRank (Test Priority)
--    Formula: rank(p) = (1-d)/N + d × ∑(rank(q)/|out(q)|)
--    d = 0.85, N = 13 pages, 30 iterations
--    File: testing/nav_graph.gleam:72-138
--    SC-UIGT-001..014
--
-- 9. Graph Density
--    Formula: density = |E| / (N × (N-1)) = 1.0 for complete digraph
--    |E| = 156 edges for 13-page navigation graph
--    File: testing/nav_graph.gleam:66-70
--
-- 10. Strongly Connected Components (SCC)
--     Result: scc_count = 1 (all pages reachable)
--     File: testing/nav_graph.gleam:145-148
--     SC-UIGT-012
--
-- 11. Chinese Postman Bound
--     Formula: CPP = |E| = 156 (minimum edges to traverse)
--     File: testing/nav_graph.gleam:140-143
--     SC-UIGT-013

-- ─── DAG & TOPOLOGICAL ALGORITHMS ───────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 12. Kahn's Algorithm (Topological Sort)
--     Complexity: O(V + E)
--     Acyclic iff processed_count = total_nodes
--     Files: verification/prometheus.gleam:48-110, ignition/dag.rs:72-80
--     SC-PROM-001, SC-BOOT-008
--
-- 13. DFS Cycle Detection (White/Gray/Black Coloring)
--     Cycle detected when Gray node re-encountered
--     File: ignition/dag.rs (via petgraph::algo::is_cyclic_directed)
--
-- 14. Wave Parallelization (Level-by-Level Partitioning)
--     Group nodes by dependency depth for parallel execution
--     File: ignition/dag.rs:82-125
--     SC-BOOT-009
--
-- 15. Path Verification
--     Check consecutive edge pairs exist in DAG
--     File: verification/prometheus.gleam:113-132
--     SC-PROM-001
--
-- 16. Set Exclusivity (Disjoint Path Constraint)
--     path_a ∩ path_b = ∅
--     File: verification/prometheus.gleam:134-144

-- ─── CRITICAL PATH METHOD (CPM) ────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 17. Forward Pass
--     ES_i = max(EF_j) for predecessors j; EF_i = ES_i + duration_i
--     File: ignition/cpm.rs:30-54
--     SC-CPM-001..010
--
-- 18. Backward Pass
--     LF_i = min(LS_j) for successors j; LS_i = LF_i - duration_i
--     File: ignition/cpm.rs:58-87
--
-- 19. Float & Critical Path
--     float_i = LS_i - ES_i; critical iff float_i = 0
--     File: ignition/cpm.rs:89-117
--     SC-BOOT-005 (boot < 60s target)

-- ─── STATE MACHINES & CONTROL ───────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 20. Hysteresis Controller (N-Consecutive Debounce)
--     States: {Unknown, Healthy, Unhealthy}
--     Transition: requires N consecutive same-checks before state change
--     Presets: Aggressive(1,1), Default(3,2), Conservative(5,3)
--     Health%: 100 × healthy_count / window_size
--     File: ignition/hysteresis.rs:99-210
--     SC-OPT-002
--
-- 21. PID Controller (Ziegler-Nichols Homeostasis)
--     Formula: output = K_p×error + K_i×∫error + K_d×d(error)/dt
--     Tuning: Ziegler-Nichols for critical damping
--     Purpose: System homeostasis (resource allocation equilibrium)
--     SC-MATH-003, SC-HOM-001..005

-- ─── CONSENSUS & VOTING ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 22. FPPS 5-Method Consensus
--     Methods: Running + PortOpen + ServiceEndpoint + QuorumVote + DigitalTwin
--     Threshold: ≥ 3/5 agree for consensus_reached = true
--     File: ignition/health_orchestra.rs
--     SC-SIL4-023
--
-- 23. 2-out-of-3 Quorum Voting
--     Formula: Q(N) = ⌊N/2⌋ + 1; for N=3: Q=2
--     File: ignition/health.rs, verification/probes.gleam:verify_2oo3
--     SC-SIL4-006, SC-QUORUM-001

-- ─── TIME SERIES & PREDICTION ───────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 24. Exponential Moving Average (EMA)
--     Formula: EMA_t = α × x_t + (1-α) × EMA_{t-1}
--     α = 0.3 (smoothing factor)
--     Timeout: EMA × 2.5 multiplier, clamped [15s, 600s]
--     File: ignition/build_oracle.rs, F# BuildHistory.fs
--     SC-IGNITE-005

-- ─── CPU MEASUREMENT & GOVERNANCE ───────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 25. CPU% Differential (/proc/stat)
--     Formula: CPU% = (active_delta / total_delta) × 100
--     active = user + nice + system + irq + softirq
--     total = active + idle + iowait
--     Window: 100ms (fast) or 1s (precise)
--     File: ignition/governor.rs:14-57
--     SC-CPU-GOV-009
--
-- 26. Adaptive Parallelism Function
--     parallelism = f(cpu_pct):
--       <60% → (16 schedulers, 16 jobs, nice 10)
--       60-70% → (12, 12, 10)
--       70-80% → (10, 10, 15)
--       80-85% → (6, 6, 19)
--       >85% → WAIT until <75%
--     File: ignition/governor.rs:97-138
--     SC-CPU-GOV-001..010

-- ─── EXPERT SYSTEMS & RULE ENGINES ──────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 27. RETE-UL Algorithm (rust-rule-engine v1.20.1)
--     Forward + backward chaining with Alpha/Beta Memory Indexing
--     Language: GRL (Grule Rule Language)
--     Performance: 2-683x speedup via zero-copy optimization
--     Facts → KnowledgeBase → RuleEvaluation → Decision
--     File: ignition/rule_engine.rs
--     SC-OODA-003

-- ─── FMEA RISK SCORING ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 28. Risk Priority Number (RPN)
--     Formula: RPN = Severity × Occurrence × Detection
--     Scale: 1-10 per factor, max RPN = 1000
--     Severity mapping: P0=9, P1=7, P2=5, P3=3
--     Gate: RPN ≥ 200 requires immediate action
--     SC-FMEA-001..008

-- ─── CATEGORY THEORY (F# MSTS Morphisms) ───────────────────────────────────
--
-- 29. Transformation Morphisms (CLR → BEAM Migration)
--     ≅ Isomorphic: 1:1 mapping, zero loss (F# Record → Gleam Custom Type)
--     ↠ Surjective: Lossy mapping (F# try/with → Gleam Result)
--     ↪ Injective: Embedded mapping (F# MailboxProcessor → Gleam OTP Actor)
--     ∅ Prohibited: Illegal in SIL-6 (mutable globals, null, unbounded recursion)
--     File: .claude/rules/c3i-gleam-msts-001.md

-- ─── STATISTICS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 30. Standard Deviation (σ)
--     Formula: σ = √(∑(x_i - μ)² / n)
--     File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:350-369
--
-- 31. Mean (μ)
--     Formula: μ = ∑x_i / n
--     File: testing/coverage_math.gleam:338-348
--
-- 32. SHA-256 Cryptographic Hash
--     Used for: Dying gasp checkpoint integrity, constitution hash
--     File: ignition/apoptosis.rs (sha2 crate)
--     SC-SIL4-007
--
-- 33. Ed25519 Digital Signature
--     Used for: Container attestation proof tokens
--     File: ignition/launch.rs (ed25519-dalek crate)
