-- =============================================================================
-- IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
-- =============================================================================

-- ─── Key Algorithms ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 1. RETE-UL (rule_engine.rs):
--    Forward + backward chaining with Alpha/Beta Memory Indexing.
--    GRL rules parsed once → KnowledgeBase → execute against Facts.
--    NOTE: Currently re-parses on every OODA cycle. SHOULD cache KnowledgeBase.
--    Performance: 2-683x speedup in v1.20.0 via zero-copy optimization.
--
-- 2. Kahn's Topological Sort (dag.rs, prometheus.gleam):
--    Iteratively removes zero-in-degree nodes. O(V+E).
--    Proves DAG acyclicity (SC-BOOT-008).
--    Rust uses petgraph crate; Gleam uses hand-rolled implementation.
--
-- 3. Critical Path Method (cpm.rs):
--    Forward pass: ES_i = max(EF_predecessors), EF_i = ES_i + dur_i
--    Backward pass: LF_i = min(LS_successors), LS_i = LF_i - dur_i
--    Critical tasks: float = LS - ES = 0. These determine minimum boot time.
--
-- 4. Exponential Moving Average (build_oracle.rs):
--    EMA_t = α×x_t + (1-α)×EMA_{t-1}, α=0.3
--    SQL UPSERT: ema = 0.3 * @dur + 0.7 * ema (F# write, Rust read-only)
--    Adaptive timeout: EMA × 2.5, clamped [15s, 600s]
--
-- 5. FPPS 5-Method Health Consensus (health_orchestra.rs):
--    Methods: Running, PortOpen, ServiceEndpoint, QuorumVote, DigitalTwin
--    Threshold: ≥3/5 agree. Each scored pass/fail independently.
--    No method weighting (all equally voted). No soft majority.
--
-- 6. Hysteresis N-Consecutive Debounce (hysteresis.rs):
--    State changes require N consecutive same-observations.
--    Sliding window for health_percentage computation.
--    Three presets: Aggressive(1,1), Default(3,2), Conservative(5,3).
--
-- 7. PageRank (nav_graph.gleam):
--    Power iteration d=0.85, 30 iterations over 13-page complete digraph.
--    Guides test execution priority (highest-ranked pages tested first).
--
-- 8. SHA-256 Dying Gasp (apoptosis.rs):
--    Hashes running_containers state before shutdown.
--    Checkpoint published to Zenoh for post-mortem verification.

-- ─── Key Design Principles ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 1. RULE-FIRST, LLM-ESCALATION:
--    GRL rules handle fast deterministic decisions (<1ms).
--    OpenRouter LLM handles novel/ambiguous situations (~2s).
--    Rule 15 (salience 40): "if NoAction AND anomaly > 0.7 → EscalateToLLM"
--
-- 2. FAIL-SAFE STATE (SC-SIL4-001):
--    Every failure mode drives toward a KNOWN SAFE state.
--    Apoptosis is the last resort: isolate → hash → gasp → drain → kill.
--    Emergency stop < 5s (SC-EMR-057).
--
-- 3. DEFENSE IN DEPTH (7-Tier Boot):
--    Each tier must be healthy before next starts (AOR-IGNITE-005).
--    Tiers 4-7 parallelize internally but serialize between tiers.
--    DAG acyclicity proven before boot begins (SC-BOOT-008).
--
-- 4. GENOTYPE/PHENOTYPE DRIFT DETECTION:
--    Digital twin holds expected state (genotype).
--    OODA observe() captures actual state (phenotype).
--    orient() computes TwinDrift for each container.
--    Rules react to drift; LLM explains multi-container drift.
--
-- 5. TRIPLE-INTERFACE MANDATE (SC-GLM-UI-001):
--    Every feature exists in 3 forms: Lustre SSR + Wisp JSON + TUI ANSI.
--    All share types from ui/domain.gleam. Feature on 1 interface = 67% incomplete.
--
-- 6. MATHEMATICAL RIGOR IN TESTING:
--    Shannon entropy ensures broad test distribution (H >= 2.5).
--    CCM weighted coverage ensures important categories tested (>= 0.90).
--    ITQS composite score gates releases (>= 0.85).
--    Graph-theory ensures navigation completeness (PageRank + CPP).
--
-- 7. OODA < 100ms SLA (SC-OODA-009, SC-BIO-001):
--    Observe: 30ms budget (podman stats polling)
--    Orient: 20ms budget (twin drift comparison)
--    Decide: 20ms budget (GRL rule evaluation)
--    Act: 20ms budget (podman command execution)
--    LLM escalation violates SLA by design (2s, logged as non-compliant).
--
-- 8. JIDOKA (SC-TPS-001):
--    Stop on defect: L0/L1/L6 failures trigger mandatory halt.
--    Signal via Zenoh: ApoptosisTriggered event published.
--    Analyze via 7-level RCA: known patterns matched first, LLM for unknowns.

-- ─── Design Patterns ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 1. RAILWAY-ORIENTED ERROR HANDLING (Rust Result<T, IgnitionError>):
--    All functions return Result. Errors propagate to main via ? operator.
--    25 IgnitionError variants cover all failure modes.
--    No unwrap() in production paths; panic = SIL-6 violation.
--
-- 2. GENETIC RESYNTHESIS (4-Way Staleness):
--    EXISTS? → INTEGRAL? → FRESH? → SKIP
--    Each container evaluated independently against 168h max age.
--    EMA predicts build duration for progress bar.
--
-- 3. CHECKPOINT-BEFORE-CHANGE:
--    Dying gasp before apoptosis.
--    State vector snapshot before tier boot.
--    Git checkpoint before risky operations (AOR-FUNC-002).
--
-- 4. PUBLISH-ON-EVERY-TRANSITION:
--    Every state change → Zenoh checkpoint message.
--    Every health check → Zenoh health topic.
--    Every OODA cycle → Zenoh OTel span.
--    Observer pattern: test runner subscribes to all topics.
--
-- 5. HYSTERESIS WRAPPING:
--    Raw health checks wrapped in hysteresis controller.
--    Prevents flapping-induced restart cascades (FMEA RPN 192).
--    Three presets selected based on environment (dev/staging/prod).
--
-- 6. ADAPTIVE PARALLELISM:
--    CPU governor measures /proc/stat (not loadavg).
--    Parallelism adjusted in 5 tiers (16→12→10→6→WAIT).
--    Hard limit 85% (SC-CPU-GOV-001).
--
-- 7. FRACTAL LAYER SEPARATION:
--    L0 = safety (can veto everything), L4 = operations (16 containers),
--    L5 = intelligence (OODA + rules + LLM), L7 = diagnostics (RCA).
--    Cross-layer coupling tracked (recovery.rs + tui.rs touch all 8 layers).

-- ─── Anti-Patterns (AVOID) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
--
-- 1. DEAD CODE MODULES:
--    openrouter.rs exists but is NEVER CALLED from any module.
--    Pattern: build → forget to wire. Fix: integration test that calls it.
--
-- 2. HARDCODED DAG:
--    launch.rs:build_dependency_graph() is hardcoded topology.
--    Adding/removing containers requires code change.
--    Fix: config-driven genome via sil6-genome.toml.
--
-- 3. RE-PARSING GRL ON EVERY CYCLE:
--    rule_engine.rs creates KnowledgeBase + parses GRL on EVERY call.
--    For <1ms SLA this wastes time. Fix: cache KnowledgeBase as static.
--
-- 4. STUBBED GUARDIAN GATE:
--    ooda_supervisor.rs:validate_with_guardian() always returns true.
--    P0 decisions (EmergencyStop, BootMesh) bypass safety check.
--    Fix: implement actual Guardian validation or fail-closed.
--
-- 5. BUG: self.observation REFERENCE:
--    ooda_supervisor.rs:207 references self.observation (doesn't exist).
--    Blocks rule engine integration. Fix: pass observation as parameter.
--
-- 6. IN-MEMORY CHECKPOINTS:
--    cascade.rs checkpoints are in-memory (lost on daemon crash).
--    Fix: persist to SQLite (build_history.db already available).
--
-- 7. SINGLE-DRIFT HANDLING:
--    rule_engine.rs:90 restarts only FIRST drifted container.
--    Multiple simultaneous drifts → only one addressed per cycle.
--    Fix: sort drifts by criticality, restart highest-priority first.
--
-- 8. NO STRUCTURED LLM RESPONSE:
--    openrouter.rs returns raw String from LLM.
--    No JSON parsing, no structured action extraction.
--    Fix: prompt for JSON response, parse into Decision enum.
--
-- 9. HEALTH CHECKS WITHOUT TREND:
--    health.rs checks are point-in-time (pass/fail).
--    No trend tracking (is health improving or degrading?).
--    hysteresis.rs partially fixes this but only for transition gating.

-- ─── Session Journal Template (SC-JOURNAL) ──────────────────────────────────
-- Every implementation session MUST produce a 13-section journal entry:
--
-- 1. Scope & Trigger — Why this work started
-- 2. Pre-State Assessment — Quantified system state before changes
-- 3. Execution Detail — What was done (batches, waves, phases)
-- 4. Root Cause Analysis — 5-Why for bugs found
-- 5. Fix Taxonomy — Categorize fixes (new module, enhancement, bugfix, wiring)
-- 6. Patterns & Anti-Patterns — What worked, what to avoid
-- 7. Verification Matrix — Pass/fail checks with method
-- 8. Files Modified — Table of file, action, lines, batch
-- 9. Architectural Observations — System-level insights
-- 10. Remaining Gaps — TODO items with priority
-- 11. Metrics Summary — Before/after metrics table
-- 12. STAMP & Constitutional Alignment — Constraint compliance
-- 13. Conclusion — Summary with key decisions
--
-- Scaling: Trivial (1-3 files) = 1-2 lines/section
--          Standard (4-15 files) = paragraphs
--          Major (15+ files) = subsections + diagrams
